nsform2D]] '''affine_inverse ( )'''Returns the inverse of the matrix.=== basis_xform ===*  [[Vector2 GD|Vector2]] '''basis_xform''' '''(''' [[Vector2 GD|Vector2]] v ''')'''Transforms the given vector by this transform's basis (no translation).=== basis_xform_inv ===*  [[Vector2 GD|Vector2]] '''basis_xform_inv''' '''(''' [[Vector2 GD|Vector2]] v ''')'''Inverse-transforms the given vector by this transform's basis (no translation).=== get_origin ===*  [[Vector2 GD|Vector2]] '''get_origin ( )'''Returns the transform's origin (translation).=== get_rotation ===*  float '''get_rotation ( )'''Returns the transform's rotation (in radians).=== get_scale ===*  [[Vector2 GD|Vector2]] '''get_scale ( )'''Returns the scale.=== interpolate_with ===*  [[Transform2D GD|Transform2D]] '''interpolate_with''' '''(''' [[Transform2D GD|Transform2D]] transform, float weight ''')'''Returns a transform interpolated between this transform and another by a given weight (0-1).=== inverse ===*  [[Transform2D GD|Transform2D]] '''inverse ( )'''Returns the inverse of the transform, under the assumption that the transformation is composed of rotation and translation (no scaling, use affine_inverse for transforms with scaling).=== is_equal_approx ===*  bool '''is_equal_approx''' '''(''' [[Transform2D GD|Transform2D]] transform ''')'''Returns {{Span|true}} if this transform and {{Span|transform}} are approximately equal, by calling {{Span|is_equal_approx}} on each component.=== orthonormalized ===*  [[Transform2D GD|Transform2D]] '''orthonormalized ( )'''Returns the transform with the basis orthogonal (90 degrees), and normalized axis vectors.=== rotated ===*  [[Transform2D GD|Transform2D]] '''rotated''' '''(''' float phi ''')'''Rotates the transform by the given angle (in radians), using matrix multiplication.=== scaled ===*  [[Transform2D GD|Transform2D]] '''scaled''' '''(''' [[Vector2 GD|Vector2]] scale ''')'''Scales the transform by the given scale factor, using matrix multiplication.=== translated ===*  [[Transform2D GD|Transform2D]] '''translated''' '''(''' [[Vector2 GD|Vector2]] offset ''')'''Translates the transform by the given offset, relative to the transform's basis vectors.Unlike [[#rotated|rotated]] and [[#scaled|scaled]], this does not use matrix multiplication.=== xform ===*  [[Variant GD|Variant]] '''xform''' '''(''' [[Variant GD|Variant]] v ''')'''Transforms the given [[Vector2 GD|Vector2]], [[Rect2 GD|Rect2]], or [[PackedVector2Array GD|PackedVector2Array]] by this transform.=== xform_inv ===*  [[Variant GD|Variant]] '''xform_inv''' '''(''' [[Variant GD|Variant]] v ''')'''Inverse-transforms the given [[Vector2 GD|Vector2]], [[Rect2 GD|Rect2]], or [[PackedVector2Array GD|PackedVector2Array]] by this transform.